//#1 - Sort 10 schools around your house by distance:
    Insertion sort.  Sample size will be relatviely small.  Simple and fast.

//#2 - eBay sorts listings by the current Bid amount:
    Merge or Quick Sort
    -class answer: Radix or Counting Sort
      since these are numbers to be sorted

//#3 - Sport scores on ESPN
    Quick Sort 
      will be most efficient
      Merge sort may be a little too much for space complexity

//#4 - Massive database (can't fit all into memory) needs to sort through past year's user data
    Merge Sort -
      good for external sorting
      plus do not want worst case O() of Quick Sort

//#5 - Almost sorted Udemy review data needs to update and add 2 new reviews
    Insertion sort
      Mostly sorted data

//#6 - Temperature Records for the past 50 years in Canada
    by Cities/Provinces or just Canada 
      if the latter, Insertion sort
        -class answer is Quick Sort due to size
      else, non-comparison sort

//#7 - Large user name database needs to be sorted. Data is very random.
    Quick Sort better space complexity than Merge sort if we have enough memory

//#8 - You want to teach sorting for the first time
    Bubble or Selection sort